Montgomery Ward stops paying some vendors - report . Montgomery Ward Holding Corp has stopped paying many of its vendors , the New York Times reported Wednesday , quoting " people familiar with the situation . " The newspaper also said merchandise financing companies had told some suppliers not to make shipments to the Chicago - based discount retailer . Montgomery Ward officials were not available for comment on the report . The report follows news that Montgomery Ward is cutting 400 corporate jobs and is in talks to sell its Signature Group direct - marketing division . ( ( - - New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1610 ) ) 
